result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:16 AM Defendant Jordan Clayton not in court.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Jordan Clayton.  Prosecuting attorney Patrick Ryan Campbell in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant could not appear today as he is currently in trial in Milwaukee County.
Court notes he is the defendant in that trial.
Based on defendant's non-appearance Court orders capias STAYED until the next court date.
Defense requests further proceedings date.
Hearing scheduled for November 9, 2022 at 09:30 am.

Case called at 10:52 AM 
District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant Jordan Clayton in court with attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez.  
Attorney Gutierrez requests another hearing date.  Court grants.  Hearing scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 10:00 am.

11:48 AM Defendant Jordan Clayton in court with attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez.  Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court calls the matter for the Defense's Motion to Dismiss Count 1 and an Arraignment.
Attorney Gutierrez presents arguments and requests to dismiss Count 1.
ADA Wittchow states that he just filed an amended complaint to remedy the issue.
Defense acknowledges receipt of amended complaint and waives reading of amended complaint.
The Court denies the Defense's Motion to Dismiss Count 1.
NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Hearing scheduled for June 22, 2022 at 10:30 am.
